La Polar Case Could Hurt Chile Spending, Central Banker Says

-- B y   R a n d y   W o o d s
-- 
2011-06-29T15:39:22Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-29/la-polar-case-could-hurt-chile-spending-central-banker-says.html
Chileans could moderate spending
after department-store operator  Empresas La Polar SA (LAPOLAR)  said this
month it had engaged in irregular lending practices, central
bank board member Enrique Marshall said in prepared remarks.  The La Polar case isn’t likely to have a “significant”
macroeconomic impact on  Chile , whose internal activity is
showing vigor, he said in a presentation posted on the bank’s
website today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Randall Woods in Santiago at 
 rwoods13@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joshua Goodman at 
